Step 1: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100
• From the income statement:
  Gross Profit = 2,861,769.51
  Total Revenue = 4,879,769.51
• Calculation:
  Gross Profit Margin = (2,861,769.51 / 4,879,769.51) × 100 ≈ 58.62%

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio.
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities
• From the cash flow statement and balance sheet:
  Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -862,455.97
  Total Current Liabilities = 624,988.48
• Calculation:
  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = -862,455.97 / 624,988.48 ≈ -1.38

Thus, the final solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "58.62%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-1.38"
  }
}
